      • getParentJoinGroup

        JoinGroupNode getParentJoinGroup()
        Return the lowest JoinGroupNode which dominates this node. Note that some kinds of IGroupMemberNodes do not appear within a JoinGroupNode context. For example, NamedSubqueryRoot and ConstructNode.
        Returns:
        The JoinGroupNode -or- null if there is no such parent join group.

      • getParentGraphPatternGroup

        GraphPatternGroup<IGroupMemberNode> getParentGraphPatternGroup()
        Return the lowest GraphPatternGroup which dominates this node. Note that some kinds of IGroupMemberNodes do not appear within a GraphPatternGroup context. For example, NamedSubqueryRoot and ConstructNode.
        Returns:
        The GraphPatternGroup -or- null if there is no such parent group.

      • getContext

        TermNode getContext()
        Return the context for the group graph pattern dominating this node.
        Returns:
        The context -or- null if there is no graph pattern dominating this node.
